{"branch":"main","confidence":92,"prompt":"PLEASE IMPLEMENT THIS PLAN:
# Protocol Audit and Integration Hardening Plan

## Summary
- Prioritize the live room/tunnel/EBT path, and include Git-over-SSB protocol/object flows in the same audit.
- Treat two current red signals separately:
  - `SSBBamboo` is materially out of sync with its own suite (`SSBBambooTests` is failing on Lipmaa math, nil/short validation, entry ID, and valid-entry verification).
  - `SSBRoomProtocolBugfixTests` has harness drift: many failures come from KVC access to a non-existent `pendingRequests` property on `SSBRoomClient`, not from the room stack itself.
- Keep deterministic integration tests as the default CI gate. Add live room smoke coverage using the existing Docker room setup, but keep that non-blocking until it is stable.

## Key Changes
- Add internal-only dependency injection for protocol tests: `SSBRoomClient` should get a non-public initializer or test extension for `SSBFeedStore`, `SSBBlobStore`, `id<SSBTransportBackend>`, and a trace sink so tests stop using shared app-state stores.
- Split room tests by layer:
  - move pure pending-request / EndErr callback behavior into `SSBMuxRPCSessionTests`;
  - keep `SSBRoomProtocolBugfixTests` for room, tunnel, discovery, and EBT behaviors only;
  - remove KVC writes to removed internals and drive behavior through `rpcSession` or explicit test seams.
- Add macOS transport/framer integration tests through `SSBTransport` with security and mux framers enabled:
  - full SHS hello/auth/accept round-trip;
  - pre-ready send buffering in `SSBSecurityFramer`;
  - partial header/body segmentation for `SSBSecurityFramer` and `SSBMuxRPCFramer`;
  - zero-length goodbye handling;
  - `SSBTunnelConnection` bidirectional loopback with real MuxRPC metadata delivery.
- Add deterministic `SSBRoomClient` integration scenarios with an in-process fake room peer:
  - `performInitialSetup`, `manifest`, `whoami`, `announce`, `room.attendants`, and `tunnel.endpoints`;
  - manifest-driven fallback and resubscribe logic;
  - tunneled `ebt.replicate`, bilateral clock exchange, and per-peer clock isolation;
  - `createHistoryStream` sync/fallback behavior.
- Replace ad hoc `/tmp/scuttle_peer_discovery.log` writes with an injectable trace sink that is mirrored to unified logging. Every trace event should include connection ID, peer ID, request ID, framer state, and direction.
- Add a dedicated scripted smoke harness under `tools/dev/` for local room runs against `docker-compose.yml`; it should assert connect, discovery, tunnel ready, EBT start, and one successful history sync and emit machine-readable traces on failure.
- Harden Git-over-SSB coverage:
  - add checked-in minimal valid `.pack` and `.idx` fixtures plus a regeneration script;
  - expand parser tests to valid lookup, fanout boundaries, large offsets, and trailer bounds;
  - expand decoder tests to valid blob/tree/commit decode plus OFS_DELTA and REF_DELTA resolution;
  - add `SSBGitObjectStore` tests for pack registration and SHA lookup;
  - expand `SSBGitRepo` tests for ref tombstones, reverse-chronological merge rules, `repoBranch` causality, and pack/index registration side effects;
  - add fake Unix-socket server tests for `git-remote-ssb.c` covering `list`, `fetch`, `push`, and malformed responses.
- Keep Git UI flows out of this pass; scope is protocol transport, object transfer, helper protocol, and repository-state reconstruction.

## Public Interfaces / Types
- No public runtime/API changes.
- Add internal test-only seams:
  - trace sink protocol or callback type;
  - non-public dependency-injected initializers/extensions for `SSBRoomClient` and only for `SSBTunnelConnection` if backend injection is needed;
  - reusable fixture builders for room events and Git pack/index blobs.

## Test Plan
- Baseline cleanup:
  - make `SSBBambooTests` green or isolate it so it no longer obscures protocol-signal;
  - make `SSBRoomProtocolBugfixTests` green by removing broken KVC assumptions.
- Default macOS CI gate:
  - raw transport;
  - macOS framer-stack integration;
  - room/tunnel/EBT deterministic integration;
  - Git pack/index/object/repo/helper tests.
- Local/manual smoke:
  - Docker room smoke with trace capture;
  - Git remote-helper round-trip against a fake app socket server.
- Acceptance scenarios:
  - room client connects, discovers peers, opens a tunnel, starts EBT, and syncs at least one feed without sleep-based polling;
  - traces are sufficient to explain failures without manual Console inspection;
  - Git state reconstruction works across multiple `git-update` messages and object lookup succeeds end-to-end from pack/index blobs.

## Assumptions
- Room/tunnel/EBT depth is the primary goal; Git-over-SSB is included but limited to protocol/object flows.
- Deterministic integration tests are PR-gating; live room/Docker smoke is informative until stabilized.
- Linux shim tests remain useful, but equivalent macOS transport/framer coverage is required because the production room path is Apple-backed.
- All new protocol integration tests use isolated temp DB/blob paths; shared app-state stores are out of scope for reliable testing."}
